place.name: NORTH BARROW
place.gazetteerText: BARROW (North), a parish in Wincanton district, Somerset; adjacent to the Wilts and Somerset railway, 3 miles SW of Castle-Cary. Post Town, Castle-Cary, under Bath. Acres, 751.-Real property, with South Barrow, £2,481. Pop., 114. Houses, 24. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £148.* Patron, Lord Portman. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
